ntal, parietal, temporal, occipital, and ethmoid bones. It plays a crucial role in the structural integrity of the skull.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efrontal\u003C/strong\u003E bone articulates with the parietal bones, sphenoid, ethmoid, and zygomatic bones.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eethmoid\u003C/strong\u003E bone primarily articulates with the frontal and sphenoid bones.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezygomatic\u003C/strong\u003E bone is not part of the neurocranium; it is part of the viscerocranium and articulates with the frontal, sphenoid, and temporal bones.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eparietal\u003C/strong\u003E bones articulate with the frontal, occipital, temporal, and sphenoid bones.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The sphenoid bone articulates with all other bones of the neurocranium.","The neurocranium consists of the frontal, parietal, temporal, occipital, sphenoid, and ethmoid bones."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64022"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17936"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64022","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64022"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T08:23:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T08:23:53+10:30"},"rela